definition: far/distant/remote/(intensifier in a comparison) by far/much (lower etc)
to wade/to be involved/to concern/to experience/to enter (classical)

sentences.english: During this period, a large number of youngers participated in the movement and went abroad.
sentences.chinese: 在這期間大批青年遠涉重洋，赴法留學。

sentences.english: Man came further futher west to stake their claim on the great American wilderness.
sentences.chinese: 人類遠涉西部，期望能征服美洲大荒野。

sentences.english: Once I travelled 7 seas to find my love .
sentences.chinese: 爲尋找吾愛我曾遠涉重洋。

sentences.english: For us, they packed up their few worldly possessions and travelled across oceans in search of a new life.
sentences.chinese: 爲了我們，他們背起行囊，遠涉重洋，尋找新的生活。

sentences.english: He went out to Australia as a French teacher.
sentences.chinese: 他遠涉重洋到澳大利亞去當法語教師。
